sql:
SELECT email
FROM users
WHERE user_id IN (SELECT user_id FROM failed_logins);

external_knowledge:
- A failed login attempt is considered as any login attempt that was not successful; 
- The last 24 hours refer to the time period between the current timestamp and 24 hours prior to it;
- The details of the last failed login attempt include the timestamp, IP address, user agent, and additional details about the attempt.

sql:
SELECT ip_address, COUNT(*) AS failed_attempts
FROM failed_logins
GROUP BY ip_address;
